The key decision here was using `CONCURRENTLY`, which builds the index in two passes with only a brief `ShareUpdateExclusiveLock` at start and end. This means all 24/7 write traffic (INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE) continued unblocked throughout the entire 3-minute build on the 500M-row table.
